  "body": "# Problem\r\nRelated to https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/11249#issuecomment-701951296\r\n\r\nWhen migration is interrupted it can fail. Migration can take long when a lot of messages are stored. The UI does not inform the user that a migration is ongoing and shows a blank screen with spinner when `Save password` is enabled. Given the relative duration and lack of system state visibility, the user is left guessing and likely to kill the app (failing migration).\r\n\r\n![Frame 1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35233054/94783979-c8625a80-03cd-11eb-8c64-ca0ed19b3a86.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n## User story\r\nAs a user I want to see what the app is doing and how long it will take so I can judge my actions (wait, switch to another app, kill app)\r\n\r\n### Requirements\r\n- Save version\r\n- Compare to check for new version when starting app\r\n- Inform user that the app is `updating` and/or `loading`, with a time approximation (reported that updating can take 'minutes')\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\nOther actions discussed in https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/11249#issuecomment-701952067\r\n\r\n\r\n## Future Steps\r\n\r\n\r\n",
